{
  "texts": [
    "The prototype used in this study was not capable of performing AO-SLO videos.",
    "Histopathology studies may help interpret our findings.",
    "Early abnormalities in diabetic retinopathy include basement membrane thickening, loss of pericytes and endothelial cells, and the followed accumulation of material inside the vascular lumen, such as invading glial cells, endothelial cell debris, pericyte ghosts, blood cells and thromboembolic material 33.",
    "These abnormalities are accompanied by capillary dilation, looping and irregularity, which appear to cause decreased blood flow, acellular capillaries, and capillary occlusion.",
    "Capillary loops have been described as varicose in shape and mainly located on the venous side on the border to avascular zones."
  ]
}